  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The Mikuli pure Java BLS cryptography implementation (based on Apache Milagro/ACML) was useful for getting Teku development started before highly optimised and standards-conforming libraries such as Blst were available.\r\n\r\nWe have retained Mikuli even after implementing Blst in order to support processor architectures not supported by Blst. However, latest Blst portable compilations have very broad support, and Mikuli is too slow to keep up with any realistically sized network these days.\r\n\r\nI propose that we should now remove the Mikuli implementation in order to reduce code complexity and maintenance overhead.",
